'''Carl Fred Sainté''' (born 9 August 2002) is a Haitian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[USL Championship]] club [[El Paso Locomotive FC|El Paso Locomotive]] and the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Club career==
Sainté is a youth product of the Haitian clubs AGE-Foot, ASGG, and finally [[Violette AC|Violette]] who he joined in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://palmes-magazine.com/amp/carl-fred-sainte-pour-la-sante-du-football-grand-goavien/|title=Carl Fred Sainté : Pour la santé du football grand-goâvien|first=Solages|last=Cénéjuste|date=30 June 2019}}</ref> He began his senior career with Violette and helped them win the 2020–21 [[Ligue Haïtienne]]. He transferred to the American club [[New Mexico United]] on 22 December 2021.<ref name="auto"/> He debuted with New Mexico United in a 2–0 [[USL Championship]] win over [[Las Vegas Lights FC|Las Vegas Lights]] on 14 March 2022, coming on as a late sub in the 87th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/627137|title=New Mexico United vs. Las Vegas Lights FC - Football Match Summary - March 13, 2022 - ESPN|website=ESPN.com}}</ref>

[[FC Dallas]] loaned Sainté to [[Phoenix Rising FC]] until the end of the season on 3 January 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phxrisingfc.com/news/phoenix-rising-signs-haitian-international-carl-sainte/ |title=Phoenix Rising Signs Haitian International Carl Sainte |first=Tyler |last=Butler |publisher=Phoenix Rising Communications |date=3 January 2025 |access-date=3 January 2025}}</ref> On 20 November, after his return to FC Dallas, the team announced that they had declined his contract option.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 November 2025 |title=FC Dallas Announces Year-End Roster Moves Ahead of 2026 |url=https://www.fcdallas.com/news/fc-dallas-announces-year-end-roster-moves-ahead-of-2026 |access-date=1 January 2026 |website=[[FC Dallas]]}}</ref>

On 19 December 2025, Sainté signed with [[El Paso Locomotive FC|El Paso Locomotive]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Morgan |first=John |date=31 December 2025 |title=El Paso Locomotive FC Sign Midfielder Carl Sainté |url=https://www.eplocomotivefc.com/news/2025/12/31/el-paso-locomotive-fc-sign-midfielder-carl-sainte/ |access-date=1 January 2026 |website=[[El Paso Locomotive FC]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Sainté represented the [[Haiti national under-17 football team|Haiti U17]]s at the [[2019 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].<ref name="auto"/> He was called up to represent the senior [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] in March 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://netalkolemedia.com/en/haiti-affrontera-le-guatemala-lors-de-la-prochaine-journee-fifa/|title=Haïti affrontera le Guatémala lors de la prochaine journée FIFA - NetAlKole Media - Restez connectés aux actualités|date=11 March 2022}}</ref> He debuted with the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] in a friendly 2–1 loss to [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]] on 27 March 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/34187/Guatemala_Haiti.html|title=Guatemala vs. Haiti|first=Benjamin|last=Strack-Zimmermann|website=www.national-football-teams.com}}</ref>

